reviews: I previously bought sunglasses from ZeroUV years ago. I've always liked them. I saw these on Amazon and for the price I had to order. It was slightly less than on their website. But when I received them they just came in a paper box. I thought there would be a microfiber sleeve cover that wouldve came with it like my previous purchase years ago. Nopes just a paper box that you're going to throw away. The fit is ok. Very dark tint. I would give 5 stars had it come in a cover or case. I had also purchased a similar version of these on Amazon which was couple bucks more but came with a microfiber cloth, sleeve cover and hard case. If u don't mind the price and dont need a cover than this purchase would be good for you.
product_name: zeroUV - Matte Black Horn Rimmed Sunglasses

review_title: Well made, cheap sunglasses with a *very* dark tint
reviews:
These glasses are *very* dark, so I find that I can only wear them on the sunniest of days. I'd rather have something that gradually tints darker towards the top for driving. Also, an effect of the style is that they don't provide my side coverage, and I find that I can see the reflection of my face in the edges. I also find them somewhat small and tight. For these reasons I regret buying these, but it was not possible to try them on before purchasing, obviously.

Despite my personal complaints, I will say that they are quite inexpensive and feel like they are decently well made.

review_title: So happy! So impressed! Buy these, you won’t regret it!
reviews: Seriously impressed! I rarely post reviews, let alone with pictures but I had to show you how amazing this is! Sunglasses are normally too big for my face so I was a little nervous to buy this without trying it on but WOW they fit so well. They’re pretty comfortable, the only con I can think of is the nose piece feel just slightly too wide for my nose, but that being said, they don’t slide off so I probably just need to get used to a looser fit compared to my old ones! They are super reflective which I love! They look super expensive but for only $20 can’t go wrong!! AND they’re polarized, even comes with a polarized tester.
